jol.types.table
Class Index

java.lang.Object
  jol.types.table.Index
All Implemented Interfaces:
java.lang.Comparable<Index>, java.lang.Iterable<Tuple>
Direct Known Subclasses:
HashIndex
public abstract class Index
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.lang.Comparable<Index>, java.lang.Iterable<Tuple>

The interface to an index structure. An index is responible for looking up tuples by some subset of tuple values identified by the index key Key.

Constructor Detail

Index

public Index(Runtime context,
             Table table,
             Key key,
             Index.Type type)
Create a new index. This constuctor will register the index with the IndexTable. The index will register a listener with the reference table.

Parameters:
context - The runtime context.
table - The table being indexed.
key - The key used to index the table.
type - The type of index being created.

lookup

public abstract TupleSet lookup(java.lang.Comparable... values)
                         throws BadKeyException
Quick way to lookup a set of values. The arity of the values must match that of the index key.

Parameters:
values - A argument list of values that should be used to perform the lookup.
Returns:
A set containing the lookup result.
Throws:
BadKeyException - If the argument values do not match the key.
